# Security Rules

## Authentication
- Argon2id for password hashing (m=19456, t=2, p=1)
- Generic error messages on auth failure
- Rate limiting on auth endpoints
- Session tokens: cryptographically secure random (32+ bytes)
- HTTP-only, Secure, SameSite=Lax cookies
- Session expiration: 7 days, refresh on use

## OAuth/OIDC
- PKCE for all OAuth flows
- State parameter (112+ bits entropy)
- Validate redirect URIs against allowlist
- Refresh token rotation
- Encrypt refresh tokens at rest
- Verify ID token signature, issuer, audience

## Authorization
- Check permissions on EVERY request
- Tenant scope on EVERY query
- Principle of least privilege
- Role-based access control
- Resource-level checks (not just route-level)

## Input Validation
- Zod for all inputs
- Validate types, lengths, formats
- Sanitize HTML (DOMPurify if rendering)
- Reject unknown fields (Zod strict)
- Limit request body size

## SQL Injection
- Drizzle ORM only
- No string concatenation in queries
- Parameterized queries always

## XSS
- React escapes by default
- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without sanitization
- CSP headers strict
- HttpOnly cookies for tokens

## CSRF
- Validate Origin header on non-GET
- SameSite=Lax cookies
- CSRF tokens for state-changing forms (if not API-only)

## Secrets
- Never in code or git
- Environment variables only
- Encrypt at rest in DB (AES-256-GCM)
- Rotate regularly
- No secrets in logs

## File Operations
- Path traversal protection (resolve + check prefix)
- MIME type validation
- File size limits
- Virus scan for user uploads (V2)
- Store outside web root

## Sandbox
- Non-root container execution
- Read-only rootfs
- Writable workspace volume only
- /tmp as tmpfs (size limited)
- No capabilities (drop ALL, add minimum)
- Network egress deny by default
- Resource limits (CPU, memory, disk, pids)
- Timeout enforcement
- Command allow/deny list

## Logging
- No passwords, tokens, or full PII
- Mask emails in logs (u**@d**.com)
- Audit security events
- Tamper-evident audit logs

## Headers
- Helmet middleware
- HSTS in production
- X-Frame-Options: DENY
- X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
- Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
- CSP strict

## Rate Limiting
- IP-based on auth endpoints
- Account-based on sensitive ops
- Per-tenant on resource-intensive ops
- Token bucket or fixed window
- Return 429 with Retry-After

## Dependencies
- Snyk/Trivy scan in CI
- Update regularly
- Pin versions
- Review changes